{
  "name": "cortical_column",
  "description": "Miniature cortical column — the repeating computational unit of neocortex. Real cortex has ~150,000 of these, each with ~80-100 neurons. Ours is a minimal version: Layer 4 (input): 2 RS receive thalamic relay. Layer 2/3 (processing): 3 RS with lateral connections and STDP for pattern learning. Layer 5 (output): 2 RS project to subcortical targets. 1 FS provides local inhibition (basket cell analog). 1 LTS provides sustained inhibition (Martinotti cell analog). Gap junctions sync the processing layer. STDP on input→processing makes columns learn to respond to specific patterns. Multiple columns compete via lateral_inhibition between them. The column that best matches input wins. Implements: feature detection, pattern classification, cortical learning.",
